ReviewText:
No one will see this review anyway, but while you're waiting for it to download to your HDD, you can make a double Krabby Patty from Sponge Bob.
You will need:
burger buns - 1
Roasted pork-beef patty - 1
Lettuce leaf - 1
Cheese slices - 1
Red onion
Tomato, about 0.7 diameter from the bun - 3 slices
Any kind of ketchup will do, however I used Heinz.
You can also choose any type of mustard.
Pickles - 5 small slices.
The order of the burger kraft is as follows:
Bottom of the bun;
The patty;
Salad;
Cheese;
Onion;
Tomato;
Ketchup;
Mustard;
Pickles;
Top of the bun
_______________
P.S. The SSD solved the booting problem :D
Don't show this review to Plankton

Pros;
Great Story & Gameplay
Smooth Frames @ 4K Resolution, Getting 80FPS Stable with a 3090ti
High Detail with the Environment and Details

Cons;
Servers are taking a dump, can't get past certain campaign missions with friends as it'll infinitely join server

For those who have EOS problem with Steam(stuck at installing dependencies stuck). Found this at the forum:

Here's a quick tutorial, with safe downloadable files, to help you access EOS on Steam: https://we.tl/t-Fglm7rOIrB

1) Restart PC;
2) Extract bat. and exe from zip archive;
3) Place it here: client_pc\root\bin\pc\EpicOnlineServices;
4) Boot up bat. file;

5) Verify integrity of game files on Steam;

6) Press Play;
7) If nothing happens press Stop and restart PC again (this will definitely work from the second attempt, but sometimes it works from the first one)

I want to be brief;

This game is fantastic. I paid $60 for a Warhammer 40K game and I was slightly worried about the price. I completed the campaign, and I believe that every dollar was WELL spent. JUST FROM THE CAMPAIGN.

I FULLY recommend this game to anyone who wants a testosterone boost.

A true masterpiece and the best W40K game I've played since the first DoW.

- Gameplay is simple yet action packed, keeps you filling with adrenaline from start to finish;
- Graphics are great and the level design is just jaw-dropping. During my gameplay sessions I was constantly stopping just to look around and enjoy the scenery. The scale of the world and the level of detail creates a lot of inmersion;
- The campaign, while a bit short, it's absolute cinema. Both the gameplay and the cutscenes offer a level of fanservice I haven't seen in quite a long time. Devs knew exactly what their audience wants.



FOR THE EMPEROR!!!

